Description: vendor/.env — OBSIDIAN_RAW_DIR relative path (subsumed by B3)
 Audit B4 (docs/260418-dual-sensitivity-analysis.md §5.2) flags
 `vendor/obsidian-wiki/.env` line 53 as defining `OBSIDIAN_RAW_DIR=_raw`
 with a relative path. In dual-zone mode this is interpreted as
 `$OBSIDIAN_VAULT_PATH/_raw`, which breaks when `_raw/` lives outside
 the vault.
 .
 Status : obsolete / subsumed.
 .
 The pilot patch B3 (`b3-vendor-env-remove`, order 3) blanks
 `OBSIDIAN_VAULT_PATH=` in the same file. Once the vault path is empty,
 the "relative OBSIDIAN_RAW_DIR resolves inside the vault" regression
 disappears transitively — there is no vault root to prepend.
 .
 Deliberate choice : this record is kept in series.json with
 `status: "obsolete"` to preserve the audit trail (so future maintainers
 see that B4 was known and consciously subsumed rather than forgotten),
 but carries NO executable diff body. Attempting `apply` or `rollback`
 against this record is a no-op / error by design. See patches/README.md
 §"How to retire a patch".
 .
 If B3 is ever reverted or narrowed, this record must be promoted back
 to `status: "active"` and its diff body regenerated to set an absolute
 `OBSIDIAN_RAW_DIR=` (or simply remove the line entirely).
